    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-30T21:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-30T21:13:00-05:00" n="28"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 28</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> message files, <gloss target="#t_FRC1"
                        >FRC</gloss> 53A278, Paris: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Administrator for Economic Cooperation (</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bissell</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <hi rend="italic">) to the Acting United States Special Representative in Europe
                        (</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_PPR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Porter</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <hi rend="italic">)</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d28fn1">Drafted by D.A. FitzGerald of the Office of the
                        Assistant Administrator, <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>; cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1">Bissell</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-30T21:13:00-05:00"
                            >October 30, 1951—9:13 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Torep1">Torep</gloss> 8159. Reference—<gloss
                        target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 5428.<note n="2" xml:id="d28fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Limit distribution to Tasca and
                        <persName corresp="#p_GL2">Gordon</persName>.</p>
                <p>1. Most encouraging to see <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> deciding put
                    real steam behind its manifesto. We most desirous cooperating every possible
                    way. In order do so however would be most desirable if we could be advised terms
                    of reference proposed committees, their composition, and expected contribution
                    from US participants. Will European participants consist of people with
                    political responsibility rather than technicians, which we believe necessary if
                    effective results likely to ensue. If European representatives to have political
                    responsibility can US make greatest contribution through technicians such as
                    Randall, Koenig and Cisler or through high level administrative officials? If
                    former, what would be relation these technicians to the three working
                    parties?</p>
                <p>2. We note housing still under Secretariat study and procedure for manpower still
                    under discussion. Unclear as to status proposed working party on agriculture. Is
                    it intended such working party be parallel and of same character as those for
                    coal, steel, power, and if so what participation by US on either technical or
                    administrative level is contemplated.</p>
                <p>3. Will expedite necessary action immediately upon receipt reply to above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRMJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bissell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
